bethmara kessler caretdown skip to content display menumenu bethmara kessler bethmara kessler senior vice president integrated global services bethmara kessler was named senior vice presidentintegrated global services igs in november  she reports to denise morrison president and chief executive officer and she is a member of the campbell leadership team bethmara leads campbell’s global shared services organization in creating value fueling growth and transforming the way campbell works igs is designed around eight operational functions that provide transactional to knowledgebased services from more than  locations around the world bethmara joined campbell as vice president corporate audit in  and she was named vice presidentstrategy and operations integrated global services in september  previously she had served as senior vice president internal audit and cochief compliance officer at warner music group before that she cofounded and worked for the fraud and risk advisory group a firm that specialized in the delivery of management consulting services for global clients she also served on the executive leadership team at limited brands where she was a key member of the team that created the company’s shared services organization and she created its continuous improvement capability bethmara earned her bachelor of business administration degree in accounting from bernard m baruch college she is a certified fraud examiner and a certified information systems auditor she is a member of the association of fraud examiners institute of internal auditors and information systems audit  control association she was named among the top  leading lesbian gay bisexual and transgender lgbt executives by the financial times in partnership with outstanding a lgbt network in  and  and among the nj biz best fifty women in business for  leadership teamdenise m morrison mark r alexander carlos j barroso edward l carolan adam g ciongoli anthony p disilvestro bob furbee bethmara kessler luc